  "title": "Group President",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>- Determine the directors of the Group’s overall strategies and business development, leading the expansion and improvement of company facilities and global operations.</p>\n<p>- Oversee all operational areas through the direct supervision of Vice-Presidents, Directors, and other senior managers.</p>\n<p>- Ensure company operations comply with all applicable international laws and regulations. Develop, approve, and implement corporate policies and procedures.</p>\n<p>- Collaborate with the executive team to drive financial performance and ensure effective resource allocation.</p>\n<p>- Keep abreast of market trends, regulatory regime, technology innovation, new commercial products in order to access market environment and market potential for partnership and investment opportunities.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>- A Bachelor's degree in a relevant field (e.g., Telecommunications, Engineering, Business, Communications).</p>\n<p>- A proven record of leadership with at least 20 years of senior management experience at a large corporation.</p>\n<p>- Top management experience in the telecommunications or related technology sector is highly desirable.</p>\n<p>- Excellent communication skills and the ability to work well with a diverse group of people, including the Board of Directors, customers, and vendors</p>",
